quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  61,10,O you who believe! shall I lead you to a commerce that will save you from the painful punishment
  61,11,"You believe in God and His messenger and strive in the way of God with your wealth and your persons, that is better for you if you (could only) know"
  61,12,"He will protectively forgive you your sins and make you enter gardens beneath which rivers flow, and pleasant dwellings in gardens of everlasting bliss, that is a great achievement"
  61,13,"And another (reward) which you love, help from God and a near victory, and convey good news to the believers"
  61,14,"O you who believe! be helpers of God: as Jesus, the Son of Mary, had said to the disciples, “Who are my helpers in (the cause of) God?” The disciples said, “We are the helpers of God.” So a party of the children of Israel believed and a party did not believe. Then We strengthened those who believed, against their enemy, so they became victorious"